{"paperId": "9d902474f238e7a0b8c6009c5eb2172fae40dd7d", "title": "Universal Language Model Fine-Tuning with Subword Tokenization for Polish", "abstract": "Universal Language Model for Fine-tuning [arXiv:1801.06146] (ULMFiT) is one of the first NLP methods for efficient inductive transfer learning. Unsupervised pretraining results in improvements on many NLP tasks for English. In this paper, we describe a new method that uses subword tokenization to adapt ULMFiT to languages with high inflection. Our approach results in a new state-of-the-art for the Polish language, taking first place in Task 3 of PolEval'18. After further training, our final model outperformed the second best model by 35%. We have open-sourced our pretrained models and code.", "venue": "arXiv.org", "year": 2018, "citationCount": 7, "influentialCitationCount": 0, "openAccessPdf": null, "tldr": {"model": "tldr@v2.0.0", "text": "A new method is described that uses subword tokenization to adapt ULMFiT to languages with high inflection, results in a new state-of-the-art for the Polish language and outperformed the second best model by 35%."}, "embedding": {"model": "specter_v2", "vector": [0.09623374044895172, 0.7833669185638428, -0.550797164440155, 0.14655767381191254, -0.5172597169876099, -0.4996773898601532, 0.5205451846122742, -0.25148698687553406, -0.7143616080284119, 0.09586435556411743, 0.7328106164932251, -0.24247537553310394, 0.1516537070274353, -0.20032906532287598, -0.21974286437034607, 0.09591806679964066, -0.1970197856426239, 0.5281722545623779, 0.03704448789358139, -0.4184870421886444, -0.3898236155509949, -0.8668156862258911, -0.3612425625324249, 0.2092197984457016, 0.2699485123157501, -0.01700110360980034, 0.4745910167694092, 0.46271631121635437, -0.8904711008071899, -0.2743176817893982, 0.4984101951122284, -0.4430623948574066, 0.16837961971759796, 0.10878530889749527, -0.9048076868057251, -0.1192503347992897, 0.3229611814022064, -0.27949145436286926, -0.24559590220451355, 0.837381541728